# Rust conventions

- `#![deny(unsafe_code)]` in new crates; no `unsafe` without approval
- Integration tests: enable `vlz/testing` feature; use per-crate `tests/` layout
- CLI output: use `write_stdout()` per CONTRIBUTING
- Unit tests: `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` in the same file or crate

## Clippy

| Situation | Command |
|-----------|---------|
| Single crate | `cargo clippy -p <crate> --all-targets -- -D warnings` |
| Cross-crate / workspace Cargo.toml | `make clippy` |
| Before PR (production behavior) | `make check-pr` (includes clippy via check-fast) |
| Before PR (non-behavior) | `make check-fast` (includes clippy) |

Do not run clippy in Cursor hooks.
